The paper deals with image quality assessment using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning models for regression tasks also suggests that it could belong to machine learning (cs.MM) and machine learning theory (cs.LG). The approach is purely data-driven, indicating that it could also belong to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on various image databases, suggesting that it could also belong to information retrieval (cs.IR).
